<br>
Rayneth Sithren was a great prophet, unsurpassed in wisdom and care. How in allthe hells would one such as you even get CLOSE to him? Methinks you're lying priest. You KNOW I disapprove..&quot; the Human sighs &quot;I guess since you choose not to cooperate, I will kill you now.&quot;<br>
<br>
Before the Human could get his spell off, Darkrayne spoke to him in Koada'Dal. &quot;I am the bastard child of Zenthra Versayth and Merthiste D'Arnak, High Priest of Innoruuk slain by the hands of your people!&quot;<br>
<br>
The Human's spell was interrupted. &quot;YOU! You are the son of Merthiste? So you are in fact the one that slew the great prophet. What an amazing find then. I shall take you back to the Feir'Dal, the rewards they will offer for your head, especially alive to torcher you themselves. My campaign to take over the monarchy of your pitiful city will be funded for the rest of my life.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;And what will you do when you take the throne Lighty? No one will accept you.&quot; Dark said. &quot;Then they shall die instead.&quot; The Human responded. &quot;You have far worse enemies to worry about then myself, by slaying me, you will achieve nothing but wasted time&quot; Dark said a flood of thought racing into his mind.<br>
<br>
&quot;Begging for you life? How degrading to your race. You should be ashamed of yourself.&quot; The Human said/<br>
&quot;It is you that will be begging for your life. For you will never claim the throne, you haven't the  man or magic power to destroy our whole race, let alone the forces that will be marching upon you through the Ambassador's daughter. Humans, Dark Elves and others alike will fight side-by-side once they realize your true identity.&quot; Dark said. &quot;How is that so priest? I see no reason why they would help the likes of you.&quot;<br>
&quot;No, not because of who we are. You are correct in that. However, you will pose a threat, genocide of one race will only lead you to have to do such a thing again and though none will care about us, they do care about themselves. All Norrath will be coming to destroy you. But you wouldn't even get Neriak, let alone anything else, why, you can't even keep one scrawny priest in your clutches.&quot; Darkrayne said running out the door that was open. The Human tried to get a spell off but it was too slow to cast. He moved out into the hall to try and snare the cleric there...but the cleric was gone...<br>
<br>
<br>
Darkrayne wearily darted into the main hallway and down the next door, he remembered this as he was dragged through the halls. Stopping at his chamber of imprisonment, he snatched up his garb and gated out of the Underground's lair and into the Bank of Neriak, surprising a few civilians of his lack of cover, which was not a priestly thing to do, Dark readied himself there.<br>
Still very weak from his beatings, Dark sat and invigored himself as well as curing his wounds. He had bought himself a little time at least. He would make his escape to Highpass. The Human would not seek him there, as the guards and Dark didn't exactly see...eye-to-eye.<br>
<br>
Dark set off, taking the river the whole way out, he soon was greeted by the earthy scent of Nek forest, and the sights and sounds were most beloved as to what he had been seeing....A faint clap of thunder and the first drop of rain dripped on Dark. Not caring this time of Karana's tomfoolery, Dark started off to Highpass.<br>
<br>
