<br>
He was going to increase rank in The Violent Harvest. <br>
<br>
He was excited..something that irked him. Excitement was for the weak...even he couldn't keep it down though so he went through with the misery. Darkrayne used his gating ability to make a fast stop near Neriak, where he visited The Grange.<br>
In the library he dug up tremendous numbers of scrolls, some of which seemed to be a bit burnt for some odd reason. <br>
<br>
More books...more scrolls. Darkrayne looked for the charter of The Violent Harvest for inside that Bible, was everything he needed to learn for the upcoming ceremony.<br>
 Muttering an unpriestly word he slammed yet another tome shut. Dust flew into his nose and he sneezed up a storm.<br>
After about an hour's worth of looking, Dark finally found The Charter...shoved in with common books...obviously the last user was either drunk when they put it away or didn't realize what they held in their hands as the book was upside down and greatly misplaced. <br>
<br>
&quot;Someone in the Triad needs to get one of the slaves to get their butts in here and clean up, this is NOT how a library should be. And WHAT in the hells is up with these burnt pages? Why are they still here if they're so important, shouldn't someone retranslate them onto a clean sheet?&quot;<br>
<br>
more gripings of that sort escaped through Darkrayne's study time as he read up on how a Harvester to be was to act at his ceremony..a very humbling experience. He still rubs his knees from kneeling so long. <br>
<br>
A paragraph caught Darkrayne's attention. <br>
<br>
&quot;The Seed-become-Harvester must swear upon their own blood, that they will abide by the Code of Conduct of the Violent Harvest, that they will remain true to the vision of the Violent Harvest, and that they will do all that they can to aid others so bound to the vision. The oath must be concluded with this, &quot;Let Innoruuk bind my blood in stone if I fail&quot;. This is the Oath of Binding.&quot;<br>
Violent Harvest Charter pg. whatever paragraph whatever <br>
<br>
&quot;Soooo...I must swear upon my blood to uphold the Harvest. I can do that. I will prepare a speech to awe even the Reaper...mayhaps I'll get a bit of a raise in my pay even&quot; *Darkrayne chuckles to himself*<br>
<br>
The following day, Darkrayne gathered with everyone at The Dragon of Hate. His helm removed and his weapon belted, as was customary being at such divine presence. <br>
Showing up late was the last thing Dark wished to do, he had had an encounter with the Underground that very day just 15 minutes before the ceremony was to begin. There was only one would-be assassin so Dark smote him down and hid the remains where some needy Troll would probably devour it. Running to the Dragon of Hate Darkrayne finally arrived, embarassed (another weakness he despised in himself) he shirked off a passing prostitute's remark of being cute and purple or something like that.<br>
<br>
At the ceremony, many things went on, his Sponsor, the now Dread Overlord Shaede gave him the rest of what he needed to do minutes before he actually had to do them. Thanking her for laying such stress on him in such timely fashion he went through the entire ceremony flawlessly...until the oath came.<br>
<br>
Being expected only to quote &quot;Let Innoruuk bind my soul in stone should I fail&quot; Darkrayne rattled off his speech smoothly...<br>
After giving the cleric a weird look, Khasirath, the Reaper of Violent Harvest, finally spoke in calm composure &quot;Repeat now the Oath priest. Let Innoruuk bind my soul in stone if i fail.&quot; <br>
<br>
Darkrayne opened his mouth to protest but could not overcome his embarassment...he turned 3 shades of purple hitting close to beet even before he stumbled about and finally blurted the oath properly.<br>
<br>
Laughter arose from the crowds but was soon silenced and the Ceremony continued...this was Darkrayne's first and last time, so he thought, that he would ingest the brew of the vine. <br>
<br>
<br>
