<br>
Pain was Darkrayne's companion, pain and the tip of the poisoned blade that remained in his body near his heart from a failed assassination attempt from The Wicked Crown.<br>
The poison was of the kind that degraded, not just one's body, but also their mind. <br>
<br>
What seemed an eternity ago, but was just two days, Darkrayne was travelling the Southern Plains of Karana. It was during one of his meditation sessions to his lord Innoruuk, that one of the Neriak underground found him...vulnerable. Stealthily creeping up to Darkrayne, he applied his poison carefully and plentifully. One slice, and it would be over, one jab, and Darkrayne would soon be his to take back to Neriak for the bounty on his head, 35,000 platinum and a title for the kidnapper of Ambassador Rylan's daughter Natori. Not to mention the additional 5,000 platinum and a finely bred war horse from the underground leader himself. The assassin, now right behind Darkrayne, reaches out to slice his throat. Darkrayne moved at the last second though, unintentionally avoiding his doom. Muttering a curse the assassin backstabbed the cleric. Spinning on his heel, unbelting his Morning star in one motion the Assassin was knocked onto his back, dazed. Darkrayne spared no moment to heal his wound, unaware of the potency of the poison in his system. Seeing the symbol of the underground, Darkrayned disposed of the assailant with one more well-placed blow to the assassin's head.<br>
<br>
It was about at this time Darkrayne realized there were still underground spies even this far into Antonica. He sought after his parter, Natori, and together they killed most if not all of the scouts this far out. It was during the eve of their last day of fighting, also the day before Natori traversed the great world of Norrath visiting Kunark and The Overthere. That Darkrayne really started feeling the effects of the poison for it was this day that the toxic brew struck his heart. Everything the cleric used to be was thrown to the wind like seeds of grass to be tossed about. Darkrayne, notorious for his unfeelingness, started experiencing weird sensations, that of frustration, anger, love, helplessness and confusion all mixed into one. Delusions and temporary dementia flashed into his mind. Darkrayne stalked off into the more forested region of Karana, there he grew dizzy and fainted not waking until the morn. <br>
<br>
Come daytime, the sounds of a lumbering treant that was VERY close woke the cleric up from his unrestful slumber.<br>
Groggily Darkrayne turned to see one headed straight his way. Readying a spell in his mind should a confrontation be imminent, Darkrayne reached fo rhis morning star...it was not there.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
